subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
Anterolateral margin of pronotum with solid black stripe reaching all or part of its extension with remaining part smoky black and narrow. Cicatrices of pronotum with concolorous punctures delimiting anterior sulci (
Fig. 18A
). Anterolateral margin not punctured. Male (
Fig. 1
A–C). Pygophore with dorsal rim sinuous and shallowly excavated (
Fig. 1A
). Superior process of genital cup elongate, elliptic with a ventral notch and adjacent to dorsal rim (
Fig. 1B
). Paramere elongate, spatulate, broad distally, anteriorly curved touching superior process of genital cup (
Fig. 1B
). Proctiger with dorsolateral tufts of setae separated by tumid ridge; posterior face subrectangular and slightly tumid (
Fig. 1B
). Ventral rim with expansion acuminate, flat, surpassing level of posterolateral angle in ventral view (
Fig. 1C
); base of each expansion with a small transverse carina. Female (
Fig. 1D
). Gonocoxites 8 posterior margin slightly sinuous, inner angle projecting over gonocoxites 9, sutural border slightly divergent distally. Gonapophyses 8 barely exposed.
